    <body>
        <title>EPPO simple figure</title>
        
        <p> A <code>fig</code> element may follow an initial <feature>paragraph</feature>, <feature>
            fragment </feature>, or <feature> fragment reference </feature> in the <feature> body
            content </feature> of a topic.</p>

    <fig>
            <title>EPPO simple figure context</title>
            <caption> <p></p> </caption>
        <graphic href="../../../graphics/figure-context.png"/>
        </fig>
        
        <section>
            <title>Structure</title>

            <p> A figure has the structure shown in the following <feature>structure diagram
            </feature>:</p>

            <fig>
                <title>Figure structure diagram</title>
                <caption><p></p></caption>
                <graphic href="../../../graphics/fig.png"/>
            </fig>

        </section>

        <section>
            <title>Example</title>
            <p> The following XML markup produces the figure that follows.</p>
            <codeblock>
<![CDATA[
        <fig>
            <title>James on his horse</title>
            <caption>
                <p>See James ride.</p>
            </caption>
            <graphic  href="../../../graphics/horse.png">
        </fig>    
]]>
            </codeblock>
            
            <fig>
                <title>James on his horse</title>
                <caption>
                    <p>See James ride.</p>
                </caption>
                <graphic href="../../../graphics/horse.png"/>
            </fig>    

        </section>
        
    </body>
